5000|$|The Law Reform Commission of Canada {{noted in}} a 1987 report that Canadian agriculture's {{increasing}} dependence on pesticides had led to inaction against many of those approved {{on the basis of}} IBT's research data. Agriculture Canada banned use of Reglone until further safety testing could be conducted and evaluated by Health and Welfare Canada, though application of the chemical continued illegally on a significant majority of lentils produced. Chlorbromuron, cyprazine, dinitramine, and phosphamidon were also banned [...] "because their manufacturers did not promise replacement studies," [...] with <b>Allidochlor</b> and Captan being restricted.|$|E

